<item>
            <title>[HBASE-12230] User impersonation does not work in &apos;simple&apos; mode.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-12230</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/hbase/blob/7cfdb38c9274e306ac37374c147a978c2cef31d6/hbase-server/src/main/java/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/security/HBasePolicyProvider.java#L54&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;code responsible for initializing proxy configuration&lt;/a&gt; does not execute unless &lt;tt&gt;&quot;hadoop.security.authorization&quot;&lt;/tt&gt; is set to true. This is departure from other Hadoop components. Impersonation should not be tied to authorization.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12747428">HBASE-12230</key>
            <summary>User impersonation does not work in &apos;simple&apos; mode.</summary>
