                            <comment id="14167659" author="adityakishore" created="Fri, 10 Oct 2014 22:20:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The attached patch makes it similar to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/hadoop-common/blob/trunk/hadoop-yarn-project/hadoop-yarn/hadoop-yarn-server/hadoop-yarn-server-resourcemanager/src/main/java/org/apache/hadoop/yarn/server/resourcemanager/ResourceManager.java#L209&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;other components in Hadoop ecosystem&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14167664" author="adityakishore" created="Fri, 10 Oct 2014 22:20:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Submitting to Hadoop QA.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14167668" author="adityakishore" created="Fri, 10 Oct 2014 22:22:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jxiang&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jxiang&quot;&gt;Jimmy Xiang&lt;/a&gt; could you please take a look?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14167699" author="jxiang" created="Fri, 10 Oct 2014 22:39:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You want to use doAs without authentication?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14167707" author="adityakishore" created="Fri, 10 Oct 2014 22:43:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Without strong, i.e. Kerberos, authentication and definitely without turning on authorization.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All other Hadoop components do not require this. Please see the link to ResouceManager code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14167717" author="adityakishore" created="Fri, 10 Oct 2014 22:50:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;And also &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/hadoop-common/blob/trunk/hadoop-common-project/hadoop-common/src/main/java/org/apache/hadoop/ipc/Server.java#L1978&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;this&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14167744" author="apurtell" created="Fri, 10 Oct 2014 23:09:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is there a use case for impersonation without authorization? Please pardon any ignorance of other Hadoop components.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14167756" author="adityakishore" created="Fri, 10 Oct 2014 23:13:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One use case could be audit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14167764" author="adityakishore" created="Fri, 10 Oct 2014 23:20:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Let&apos;s assume that an organization has set up authentication at the REST gateway which is the only entry point into the Hadoop/HBase cluster and hence would like to not enable security inside the cluster. They also want to carry the identity of the user that they verified at the REST gateway to the HBase service for audit purpose.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Even HBase RPC advertises &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/hbase/blob/master/hbase-server/src/main/java/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/ipc/RpcServer.java#L1769&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;this&lt;/a&gt; but fails since the proxy group configuration was not loaded at the time of initialization.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
